Located in the heart of the Garden District, the Parks-Bowman Mansion is a classic example of the good life in New Orleans.  Shaded by palm trees and a live oak, the deep porches on all three levels tempt you to rest and relax. description: A third-floor oasis in the heart of the Garden District. description: The Sully Mansion is located just one block off St. Charles Ave. in the New Orleans Garden District! You can't beat this location and all of our amenities. Walking distance from anything and everything New Orleans! The Sully Mansion was designed by renowned architect Thomas Sully in 1890 and embodies the unique architectural look of Uptown New Orleans. Nestled in the heart of the historic New Orleans Garden District, our inn is surrounded by live oaks, lush gardens, and wrought iron fences.   The inn has nine guest rooms; three on the first floor and six on the second floor.
